    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="522"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/396</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Netherland Chargé</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Beaufort</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1918</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to inform
                    Your Excellency that in order to be able to answer in an unqualified manner the
                    doubts expressed in all directions concerning the intentions of the Associated
                    Governments, my Government has instructed me to ask the American Government to
                    be good enough to give me the formal assurance that from the 20th of last March
                    no vessel flying the Dutch flag will be seized or detained in a port of the
                    United States.</p>
                <p>In consequence of the foregoing, I have the honor to have recourse to the
                    obliging good offices of Your Excellency in order to obtain as soon as possible
                    from the Government of the United States the assurance asked for by my
                    Government.</p>
                <p>In thanking Your Excellency in advance for the attention which you will be good
                    enough to give to my request, I take this opportunity to renew the assurances of
                    my highest consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. de Beaufort</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
